value.value: Catalysis of the reaction: UDP-galactose + lipopolysaccharide = UDP + 1,6 alpha-D-galactosyl-lipopolysaccharide.
Catalysis of the reaction: a long-chain fatty acid + ATP + holo-[ACP] = a long-chain fatty acyl-[ACP] + AMP + diphosphate. A long-chain fatty acid has an aliphatic tail containing 13 to 22 carbons.

definition.value: While there is not universal consensus on the lengths of short-, medium-, long- and very-long-chain fatty acids, the GO uses the definitions in ChEBI (see CHEBI:26666, CHEBI:59554, CHEBI:15904 and CHEBI:27283).

value.value: Catalysis of the reaction: L-lysine + H+ = cadaverine + CO2.
Catalysis of the reaction: (S)-malate + a quinone = oxaloacetate + a quinol. Vitamin K (menaquinone) and several other quinones can act as acceptors.
Catalysis of the reaction: acetyl-CoA + maltose = CoA + acetyl-maltose.
Catalysis of the reaction: D-mannitol 1-phosphate + NAD+ = D-fructose 6-phosphate + NADH + H+.

definition.value: Note that this term has a MetaCyc pathway reference as the pathway only has a single step.

value.value: Catalysis of the reaction: D-mannonate = 2-dehydro-3-deoxy-D-gluconate + H2O.
Catalysis of the reaction: alpha-D-mannose 1-phosphate + GDP + H+ = GDP-alpha-D-mannose + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction: glycerone phosphate = methylglyoxal + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction: methylthioadenosine + H2O = adenine + 5-methylthio-D-ribose.

Catalysis of the specific cleavage of the beta-(1->4) glycosidic linkage between N-acetylmuramyl and N-acetylglucosaminyl residues in peptidoglycan, with the concomitant formation of 1,6-anhydro-N-acetylmuramyl residues. Acts on linkages within peptidoglycan chains (i.e. not at the ends) to produce shorter strands with 1,6-anhydromuramic acid ends.

Catalysis of the specific cleavage of the beta-(1->4) glycosidic linkage between N-acetylmuramyl and N-acetylglucosaminyl residues in peptidoglycan, with the concomitant formation of 1,6-anhydro-N-acetylmuramyl residues.
Catalysis of the reaction: 1D-myo-inositol 1-phosphate + H2O = myo-inositol + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction: 2-succinylbenzoyl-CoA + H+ = 1,4-dihydroxy-2-naphthoyl-CoA + H2O.
Catalysis of the reaction: nicotinamide + H2O = nicotinate + NH3.
Catalysis of the reaction: reduced ferredoxin + NAD(P)+ = oxidized ferredoxin + NAD(P)H + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction: S-adenosyl-L-methionine(1+) + nicotinate = N-methylnicotinate + S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine.
Catalysis of the reaction: 5,6-dimethylbenzimidazole + nicotinate D-ribonucleotide = alpha-ribazole 5'-phosphate + H+ + nicotinate.
Catalysis of the reaction: nitrite + acceptor = nitrate + reduced acceptor.
Catalysis of the reaction: 2 NO + 2 O2 + NAD(P)H + H+ = 2 nitrate + NAD(P)+.

definition.value: Note that this activity is similar to nitric oxide dioxygenase activity, heme protein ; GO:0141118, but GO:0141118 uses a heme protein as the electron donor.

value.value: Catalysis of the reaction: NH4+ + 3 NAD(P)+ + 2 H2O = nitrite + 3 NAD(P)H + 5 H+.
Catalysis of the exonucleolytic cleavage of oligonucleotides to yield nucleoside 5'-phosphates.

definition.value: Note that enzymes with this activity usually also hydrolyze NAD+ to NMN and AMP.

value.value: Catalysis of the reaction: H+ + oxaloacetate = CO2 + pyruvate.
Catalysis of the reaction: H+ + oxalyl-CoA = CO2 + formyl-CoA.
Catalysis of the reaction: a palmitoleoyl-[acyl-carrier protein] + alpha-KDO-(2->4)-alpha-KDO-(2->6)-lipid IVA = KDO2-(palmitoleoyl)-lipid IVA + a holo-[acyl-carrier protein].
Catalysis of the reaction: penicillin + H2O = a carboxylate + 6-aminopenicillanate.

Catalysis of the reaction: [GlcNAc-(1->4)-Mur2Ac(oyl-L-Ala-gamma-D-Glu-L-Lys-D-Ala-D-Ala)](n)-di-trans,octa-cis-undecaprenyl diphosphate + beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->4)-Mur2Ac(oyl-L-Ala-gamma-D-Glu-L-Lys-D-Ala-D-Ala)-di-trans,octa-cis-undecaprenyl diphosphate = [GlcNAc-(1->4)-Mur2Ac(oyl-L-Ala-gamma-D-Glu-L-Lys-D-Ala-D-Ala)](n+1)-di-trans-octa-cis-undecaprenyl diphosphate + di-trans,octa-cis-undecaprenyl diphosphate + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction: 2-phenylacetaldehyde + H2O + NAD+ = 2-phenylacetate + 2 H+ + NADH.
Catalysis of the reaction: acetyl-CoA + phosphate = CoA + acetyl phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction: phosphatidylglycerol + membrane-derived-oligosaccharide D-glucose = 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol + membrane-derived-oligosaccharide 6-(glycerophospho)-D-glucose.
Catalysis of the transfer of the diacylglyceryl group from phosphatidylglycerol to the sulfhydryl group of the prospective N-terminal cysteine residue in an unmodified prolipoprotein.
Catalysis of the reaction: phosphatidylglycerophosphate + H2O = phosphatidylglycerol + phosphate.

Catalysis of the reaction: di-trans,octa-cis-undecaprenyl phosphate + UDP-N-acetyl-alpha-D-muramoyl-L-alanyl-gamma-D-glutamyl-L-lysyl-D-alanyl-D-alanine = Mur2Ac(oyl-L-Ala-gamma-D-Glu-L-Lys-D-Ala-D-Ala)-di-trans,octa-cis-undecaprenyl diphosphate + UMP.

definition.value: Note that EC classifies all three 'UDP-N-acetylmuramoyl-L-alanyl-D-glutamyl-meso-2,6-diaminopimelyl-D-alanyl-D-alanine:undecaprenyl-phosphate transferase activity ; GO:0051992' and 'phospho-N-acetylmuramoyl-pentapeptide-transferase activity ; GO:0008963' under EC:2.7.8.13.

value.value: Catalysis of the reaction: phosphate + oxaloacetate = phosphoenolpyruvate + HCO3-.
Catalysis of the reaction: phosphoenolpyruvate + protein L-histidine = pyruvate + protein N(pi)-phospho-L-histidine.
Catalysis of the reaction: alpha-D-glucosamine 1-phosphate = D-glucosamine 6-phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction: 2-phosphoglycolate + H2O = glycolate + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction: D-sedoheptulose-7-phosphate = D-alpha,beta-D-heptose 7-phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction: a 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine + H2O = a 2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine + a fatty acid + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + 4-amino-2-methyl-5-phosphomethylpyrimidine = ADP + 4-amino-2-methyl-5-diphosphomethylpyrimidine.
Catalysis of the reaction: D-ribose 1-phosphate = D-ribose 5-phosphate. Also converts 2-deoxy-alpha-D-ribose 1-phosphate into 2-deoxy-D-ribose 5-phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction: D-ribulose 5-phosphate + ATP = D-ribulose 1,5-bisphosphate + ADP + 2 H+.
Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + phosphate(n) = ADP + phosphate(n+1).
Catalysis of the reaction: NAD+ + prephenate = (4-hydroxyphenyl)pyruvate + CO2 + NADH.

Catalysis of the integration of prophage DNA into a target DNA molecule, usually a bacterial chromosome, via a sequence-specific recombination event which involves the formation of an intasome, a DNA-protein-complex designed for site-specific recombination of the phage and host DNA.
Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + propanoate = ADP + propanoyl phosphate.

Catalysis of the PEP-dependent, phosphoryl transfer-driven transport of substances across a membrane. The transport happens by catalysis of the reaction: protein N-phosphohistidine + sugar(out) = protein histidine + sugar phosphate(in). This differs from primary and secondary active transport in that the solute is modified during transport.

Catalysis of the reaction: S-adenosyl-L-methionine + protein L-glutamate = S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + protein L-glutamate 5-methyl ester; this reaction is the methylation of peptidyl-L-glutamate to form peptidyl-L-glutamate 5-methyl ester.
Catalysis of the reaction: protein L-glutamate O(5)-methyl ester + H2O = protein L-glutamate + methanol.
Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + H2O + pyruvate = AMP + 2 H+ + phosphate + phosphoenolpyruvate.
